			Profile
			
			Dong-QiangLin,male,biochemicalengineer,graduatedfromtheDepartmentofChemicalEngineering,ZhejiangUniversityin1992,andthenobtainedthePhD.Degreein1997.Since1998,heworkforZhejiangUniversity,andbecameaprofessorattheDepartmentofChemicalandBiologicalEngineeringin2007.NowheisthedirectoroftheInstituteofBiosengineering.Healsoworkedaspost-doctorattheInstituteofEnzymeTechnology,DuesseldorfUniversityin1999-2001,and&nbsp;asthevisitingscholaratStuttgartUniversity(2004.8-10,2005.6-8),JacobUniversityBremen(2009.1-4)andRensselaerPolytechnicInstitute(2014-10-11).Tillnowhehaspublishedmorethan160papersandthreebooks,andwasauthorized&nbsp;28patents.Hegotseveraltechnicalawards,suchastheFirstAwardofTechnologyProgress(EducationMinistryofChina),SecondAwardofTechnologyProgress(ZhejiangProvince)andFirstAwardofTechnologyProgressinHighEducation(EducationCommitteeofZhejiangProvinceofChina).Inrecentyearhefocusedonnovelbioseparationtechnology,separationmaterials,computersimulationandbioprocessdesign.&nbsp;TheresearchworksweremainlysupportedbytheNationalNaturalScienceFoundationofChina,theProgramforNewCenturyExcellentTalentsinUniversity,theHi-techResearchandDevelopmentProgramofChina(863Program)andtheNationalBasicResearchandDevelopmentProgramofChina(973Program).
